{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-timothy.2",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Timothy 2 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:1",
      "text": "I exhort therefore, first of all, that petitions, prayers, intercessions, and givings of thanks be made for all men,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:2",
      "text": "for kings and all who are in high places, that we may lead a tranquil and quiet life in all godliness and reverence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:3",
      "text": "For this is good and acceptable in the sight of God our Savior,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:4",
      "text": "who desires all people to be saved and come to full knowledge of the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:5",
      "text": "For there is one God and one mediator between God and men, the man Christ Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:6",
      "text": "who gave himself as a ransom for all, the testimony at the proper time,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:7",
      "text": "to which I was appointed a preacher and an apostle— I am telling the truth in Christ, not lying — a teacher of the Gentiles in faith and truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:8",
      "text": "I desire therefore that the men in every place pray, lifting up holy hands without anger and doubting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:9",
      "text": "In the same way, that women also adorn themselves in decent clothing, with modesty and propriety, not with braided hair, gold, pearls, or expensive clothing,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:10",
      "text": "but with good works, which is appropriate for women professing godliness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:11",
      "text": "Let a woman learn in quietness with full submission.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:12",
      "text": "But I don’t permit a woman to teach, nor to exercise authority over a man, but to be in quietness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:13",
      "text": "For Adam was formed first, then Eve.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:14",
      "text": "Adam wasn’t deceived, but the woman, being deceived, has fallen into disobedience;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-timothy.2.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 2:15",
      "text": "but she will be saved through her childbearing, if they continue in faith, love, and holiness with sobriety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
